item.title: Quote 1
item.description: Macbeth Act 1 Quotes Review This is a review to help you for future quotations tests. For EACH of the following quotations from Macbeth, please answer the following: the speaker (1 mark) the context (where does the phrase occur in the plot/action?) (1 mark) the meaning (paraphrase the quote—put it into your own words) (1 mark) the significance of the quote (explain its importance through character, theme, or descriptive language (2 marks) Further questions to reflect and answers for question 4: How is the quote significant or important in terms of plot? Foreshadowing? What does this quote tell us about the character of the speaker? How does this quotation relate to a theme(s) of the play? (see Theme sheet) How does the descriptive language help us to understand what the character is saying? ACT 1 “That, trusted home,/Might yet enkindle you unto the crown,/Besides the thane of Cawdor.
